Description: This graphic describes what LiteLLM does as a Python pip install. After invoking install, it copies something to site-packages. From there, any invocation of Python spins off a background process, where it collects sensitive info like credentials for all things it can access. It then spins up a service for persistence. It encrypts all of the data, and then exfils it to a website. The service polls every 50 mins and pulls new binaries and executes them as requested.
