URL reference: https://www.nivelepsilon.com/2023/12/17/simplifying-stateful-application-management-with-operators/
DateReviewed: 2026-04-11
Description: Our article today is going to talk about using operators to help with Kubernetes app states. We start with background - in this case comparing a conductor to what Kubernetes does - in paticular, operators. We then dive in with what is an operator - which is an app specific controller to help manage a K8s app. The idea is that an operator knows what it's app needs, storage, runtime, install and update wise. They then talk about the differences between stateless and stateful apps - starting with stateless. This is easy, as we just need to run the image and have the number of copies/replicas as requested -- no special handling needed. For stateful, you need to keep the data safe -- which makes running, stopping and replacing pods more work. For instance, with a DB, you'd need to save the DB on exit, and restore it on pod creation, along with other things. The authors argue this makes life simpler.
BottomLine: Exploration of what a Kubernetes Operator does at a high level
